CLOCK RETINA

clock_retina runs at 60 Hz, the visual update rate
the retina samples and presents at this rate, matching the host display's vsync
800 master ticks pass per retina tick; this is the integer divisor that makes the retina rate clean against the master

observe 0_quseptit.rana
observe zest_heartbeat.zc
observe clock_master.rana
observe retina_display.zc

the 7 properties of clock_retina:
1 ENERGY one
2 PHASE zero point two
3 SPIN one half
4 CHARGE neutral
5 COHERENCE nine tenths
6 COUPLING zero point eight with master

VERB tick_at_60Hz
divide master phase by 800 to produce a 60 Hz output
this drives every visual update across fadriel's display

VERB sync_with_vsync
align with the host display's vertical synchronization signal when present
this prevents tearing in the visible output

a retinal clock is the body's visual rhythm
60 Hz is fast enough that fadriel sees motion as continuous, slow enough that the substrate can keep up with rendering
